title: NSW Police search property believed to be linked to grandfather's kidnapping
description: NSW Police have searched a property in Dural believed to be linked to the kidnapping of 85-year-old Chris Baghsarian. #dural #crime #sydney #nswpolice

title: Kids under 12 to be banned from riding e-bikes in NSW this year
description: Children under the age of 12 will be banned from riding e-bikes by the end of the year under new legislation introduced by the NSW government. #bike #ebike #sydney #nsw #nswpol

title: New research into Mounjaro's effects on patients with asthma
description: A new study is exploring whether weight loss jab Mounjaro reduces asthma symptoms in people with obesity. #mounjaro #weightloss #asthma #obesity #health

title: What happens next after Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor's arrest?
description: Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor has been released from custody after being arrested on suspicion of misconduct in public office. Foreign Editor Hugh Whitfeld breaks down what happens next for the former prince, and whether police will lay criminal charges. #princeandrew #royals #royalfamily #arrest #police

title: Major breakthrough in grandfather kidnapping case | 7NEWS
description: Sydney detectives have raided a 20,000 square metre property on Wildthorn Avenue in Dural, believed to be where 85-year-old grandfather Chris Bagzarian was held captive after being kidnapped from his North Ryde home. Police linked kidnapping videos circulating in the underworld to features inside the property, which had been vacant for at least six months. Investigators maintain Mr Bagzarian was a victim of mistaken identity, with texts circulating in the underworld suggesting the wrong person was targeted. title: Four teens charged over NRL star shooting | 7NEWS
description: Four teenagers have been arrested and charged over attacks targeting former NRL player Matt Utai and properties linked to his son Iziah in Sydney's south west. The incidents include a shooting of Matt Utai on Tuesday, a firebombing in Guildford West, and a shooting at a St Clair house, believed to stem from a feud between the Coconut Cartel and the Alameddine crime organisation. Police conducted six search warrants across five suburbs, seizing a kilogram of cocaine and laying 12 charges, though the person who shot Matt Utai remains at large. title: Coalition demands passport cancellations for ISIS brides | 7NEWS
description: The federal Coalition opposition is calling on Foreign Minister Penny Wong to cancel the passports of ISIS brides seeking to return to Australia from Syria's Roj refugee camp. The government has placed a temporary exclusion order on one of 11 women, but the rest remain free to return with their children. Former Home Affairs Secretary Mike Pezzullo says the laws don't need changing, but the focus should be on monitoring the families when they return to Australia. title: Trump's Board of Peace meets amid Iran strike threats | 7NEWS
description: US President Donald Trump has convened the inaugural meeting of his Board of Peace in Washington, bringing together representatives from 47 nations to oversee Gaza's security and reconstruction following the war with Israel. The meeting occurs amid a significant US military buildup in the Middle East, including fighter jets, destroyers, submarines and aircraft carriers, as Trump threatens potential strikes against Iran within 10 days if no deal is reached on its nuclear programme. title: Hunt for hit-run driver in South Kingsville | 7NEWS
description: A 41-year-old pedestrian was struck by a vehicle on Blackshaws Road in South Kingsville, Melbourne's inner west, around 11pm. The driver accelerated away from the scene, leaving the victim bleeding in the gutter with serious injuries. Police are searching for the vehicle, which is likely to have damage from the impact, and appealing for witnesses to come forward. title: Greg Lynn applies for bail awaiting murder retrial | 7NEWS
description: Former Jetstar pilot Greg Lynn has applied for bail while awaiting retrial for the alleged murder of 73-year-old camper Carol Clay in Victoria's High Country in March 2020. Lynn was initially convicted of murdering Clay but was acquitted on appeal, while a jury found him not guilty of murdering Clay's boyfriend Russell Hill. A retrial date has not yet been set. title: NSW bans children under 12 from riding e-bikes | 7NEWS
description: New South Wales will ban children under 12 from riding e-bikes by the end of the year, with a transport review investigating whether to raise the age limit to 16. The government will adopt a European standard limiting e-bikes to 250 watts from 2029, giving current owners of the estimated 760,000 e-bikes in NSW time to comply. The new regulations, expected to be backed by fines, include anti-tampering measures to prevent modification of power and speed. title: Australia's $175 billion generational wealth transfer | 7NEWS
description: Almost two-thirds of Australians expect to leave an inheritance, with approximately $175 billion annually set to be transferred from those over 60 to younger generations over the next couple of decades. Children are the primary beneficiaries, with two in three people planning to leave assets to their kids, though this trend is expected to exacerbate wealth inequality between those who receive inheritances and those who don't. Financial experts recommend paying off high-interest debt first, investing wisely, and having updated wills with professional legal advice to avoid family disputes. title: Bunnings and Kmart spending spree raises inflation fears | 7NEWS
description: Australians spent $17 billion at Bunnings and Kmart over six months, delivering owner Wesfarmers a $1.6 billion profit despite ongoing cost-of-living pressures. Economists warn the significant spending surge at these major retail chains could contribute to rising inflation and potentially push up interest rates. title: Nedd Brockmann launches rescue dog run club | 7NEWS
description: Young Australian of the Year Nedd Brockmann launched the Petbarn Foundation's Rescue Mission Run Club at Rushcutters Bay Park in Sydney's east, bringing together hundreds of runners and rescue dogs for a special sunrise run. The event encourages Australians to dedicate their morning runs to rescue dogs awaiting adoption. The gathering demonstrated how rescue dogs can serve as ideal running companions, featuring enthusiastic canines and their human participants. title: Mount Kanlaon volcano erupts in the Philippines | 7NEWS
description: Mount Kanlaon volcano in the Philippines erupted with a dramatic two-minute explosion, blasting plumes of smoke and ash approximately 2000 metres into the sky and triggering ashfall in nearby towns. Authorities issued an emergency alert and deployed response teams to affected areas. The active volcano has erupted more than 40 times since 1866, including a deadly 1996 blast that killed three hikers.
